ove error classes when values have been entered\";s:14:\"#default_value\";s:1:\"1\";s:12:\"#description\";s:242:\"If an element has a <code>.has-error</code> class attached to it, enabling this will automatically remove that class when a value is entered. This feature compliments the \"General > Forms > Make required elements display as an error\" feature.\";}}s:8:\"popovers\";a:7:{s:5:\"#type\";s:8:\"fieldset\";s:6:\"#title\";s:8:\"Popovers\";s:12:\"#description\";s:104:\"Add small overlays of content, like those on the iPad, to any element for housing secondary information.\";s:12:\"#collapsible\";b:1;s:10:\"#collapsed\";b:1;s:25:\"bootstrap_popover_enabled\";a:4:{s:5:\"#type\";s:8:\"checkbox\";s:6:\"#title\";s:16:\"Enable popovers.\";s:12:\"#description\";s:281:\"Elements that have the <code>data-toggle=\"popover\"</code> attribute set will automatically initialize the popover upon page load. <strong class=\"error text-error\">WARNING: This feature can sometimes impact performance. Disable if pages appear to \"hang\" after initial load.</strong>\";s:14:\"#default_value\";s:1:\"1\";}s:7:\"options\";a:16:{s:5:\"#type\";s:8:\"fieldset\";s:6:\"#title\";s:8:\"Opciones\";s:12:\"#description\";s:180:\"These are global options. Each popover can independently override desired settings by appending the option name to <code>data-</code>. Example: <code>data-animation=\"false\"</code>.\";s:12:\"#collapsible\";b:1;s:10:\"#collapsed\";b:1;s:7:\"#states\";a:1:{s:7:\"visible\";a:1:{s:40:\":input[name=\"bootstrap_popover_enabled\"]\";a:1:{s:7:\"checked\";b:1;}}}s:27:\"bootstrap_popover_animation\";a:4:{s:5:\"#type\";s:8:\"checkbox\";s:6:\"#title\";s:7:\"animate\";s:12:\"#description\";s:43:\"Apply a CSS fade transition to the popover.\";s:14:\"#default_value\";s:1:\"1\";}s:22:\"bootstrap_popover_html\";a:4:{s:5:\"#type\";s:8:\"checkbox\";s:6:\"#title\";s:4:\"HTML\";s:12:\"#description\";s:151:\"Insert HTML into the popover. If false, jQuery\'s text method will be used to insert c